\i0  means simply that money on hand now is worth more than money to be received in the future. Do you remember the old saying, \'93A bird in the hand is worth two in the bush\'94? For an investor, a dollar in hand is usually worth more today because it can be invested and earn interest going forward. The \'93time value of money\'94 concept is an important one to understand because the value of any business is simply the amount of cash it can generate over its lifetime, discounted back to the present day. This topic will be discussed in greater detail in Chapter 6.\cb1 \
